cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.NI, cs.HC

The paper focuses on the privacy risks associated with public WiFi hotspots and their captive portals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the data collection and tracking behaviors of these hotspots, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The use of social login and registration forms also suggests a possible fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the technical aspects of the data collection and tracking, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
